OL,3,CMPs debate removal of immunity
OL,4,Cprovision from Legacy Act
OL,6,FLabour has introduced its Troubles
OL,7,FBill to replace the Act and end the
OL,8,Fimmunity scheme in that legislation,
OL,9,Fwhich was ruled unlawful in the courts
OL,10,Fand has never been commenced.
OL,12,FThe scheme would have allowed
OL,13,Fperpetrators of Troubles-related
OL,14,Fcrimes to be given immunity from
OL,15,Fprosecution in exchange for co-
OL,16,Foperation with a truth recovery body.
OL,18,FThe Government's Remedial Order also
OL,19,Fseeks to remove the bar on new civil
OL,20,Fclaims over Troubles cases.
